    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gray or whitish patch, sheet, or layered clouds which almost always have dark tessellations (honeycomb appearance), rounded masses or rolls. Except for virga they are non-fibrous and may or may not be merged. They also have regularly arranged small elements with an apparent width of more than five degrees (three fingers - at arm's length).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
